  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Rinse the <strong>sushi rice</strong> in a sieve under <strong>cold running water</strong> for 30 secs (use your hands to really wash the grains!), then set aside to drain fully</p><p>Add the <strong>drained rice</strong> with 200ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong>, the<strong> creamed coconut </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Tip: Don't let the water fully boil as this will make the rice stick to the pot!</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1650991108702-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1650991108702-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1650991108702-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1650991108702-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1650991108702-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to low until very gently bubbling and cook, covered, for 15 min</p><p>Once the rice is cooked, remove the pot from the heat, add the <strong>blanched peas </strong>and give everything a good mix up until the peas are warmed through and the coconut cream is fully incorporated</p><p>Keep covered for a further 10 min before serving – this is your <strong>sticky coconut rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1650991127686-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1650991127686-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1650991127686-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1650991127686-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1650991127686-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, pat the <strong>tilapia fillets</strong> dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Add the the <strong>cornflour</strong> to a plate with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>tilapia fillets</strong> to the plate and press them into the <strong>seasoned cornflour </strong>until fully coated, then tap off the excess</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1650991131316-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1650991131316-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
